== ENGLISH ==

=== Pronunciation ===

'''Ap-proxi-mate-ly'''

AHD phonetic symbols: [ă-prŏksə-mĭt-lē]


=== Adverb ===

'''Approximately''' (abbr. ''approx.'')
Word breaks: Ap-proxi-mate-ly

*Used (usually) in giving measurements to denote a level of impreciseness or slight margin of error possible in that value (ie. Indicates an estimate if the precise value is not known).

Approximate wieght on industrial packages is shown as "'''e'''"

''Synonym:'' [[Around]], [[near]], [[nearly]], [[almost]], [[about]], [[loosely]], [[roughly]], close to.

''Antonym:'' [[Accurately]], [[definitely]], [[exactly]], [[precisely]]
==== Related Terms ====

*[[Approximate]]

==== Examples ====

#In every box of matches there is ''approximately'' 40 matchsticks.
#Per 100g of chocolate there is ''approximately'' 11.6g of saturated fat.
